  \n  \n    Do not post: \n    \n  Threats that could lead to death (and other forms of high-severity violence) of any target(s) where threat is defined as any of the following:\n\n      \n              Statements of intent to commit high-severity violence; or \n        Calls for high-severity violence including content where no target is specified but a symbol represents the target and\/or includes a visual of an armament to represent violence; or \n        Statements advocating for high-severity violence; or \n        Aspirational or conditional statements to commit high-severity violence \n     \n      \n      Content that asks or offers services for hire to kill others (for example, hitmen, mercenaries, assassins) or advocates for the use of a hitman, mercenary or assassin against a target. \n     \n      Admissions, statements of intent or advocacy, calls to action, or aspirational or conditional statements to kidnap a target. \n     \n   Threats that lead to serious injury (mid-severity violence) towards private individuals, minor public figures, high risk persons, or high risk groups where threat is defined as any of the following:\n\n      \n Statements of intent to commit violence; or \n        Statements advocating violence; or \n        Calls for mid-severity violence including content where no target is specified but a symbol represents the target; or \n        Aspirational or conditional statements to commit violence; or  \n   Content about other target(s) apart from private individuals, minor public figures, high risk persons, or high risk groups and any credible:\n      \n     \n          Statements of intent to commit violence; or \n          Calls for action of violence; or \n          Statements advocating for violence; or \n       Aspirational or conditional statements to commit violence \n   \n    \n\n      Threats that lead to physical harm (or other forms of lower-severity violence) towards private individuals (self-reporting required) or minor public figures where threat is defined as any of the following:\n         \n      \n            Private individuals (name and\/or face match are required) or minor public figures that includes:\n          \n       \n                Statements of intent, calls for action, advocating, aspirational or conditional statements to commit low-severity violence  \n              \n      \n    \n     Imagery of private individuals or minor public figures that has been manipulated to include threats of violence either in text or pictorial (adding bulls eye, dart, gun to head, etc.) \n        Any content created for the express purpose of outing an individual as a member of a designated and recognizable at-risk group \n        Instructions on how to make or use weapons if there\u2019s evidence of a goal to seriously injure or kill people, through:\n     \n          \n            Language explicitly stating that goal, or \n            Photos or videos that show or simulate the end result (serious injury or death) as part of the instruction \n            Unless the aforementioned content is shared as part of recreational self defense, for military training purposes, commercial video games, or news coverage (posted by Page or with news logo) \n          \n      \n     \n      Providing instructions on how to make or use explosives:\n         \n          \n            Unless there is clear context that the content is for a non-violent purpose (for example part of commercial video games, clear scientific\/educational purpose, fireworks, or specifically for fishing) \n          \n      \n   Any content containing statements of intent, calls for action, or advocating for high or mid-severity violence due to voting, voter registration, or the outcome of an election \n        Misinformation and unverifiable rumors that contribute to the risk of imminent violence or physical harm. \n      Statements of intent or advocacy, calls to action, or aspirational or conditional statements to bring weapons  to locations, including but not limited to places of worship,educational facilities or polling places ( or encouraging others to do the same). \n     \n     \n     \n         \n    \n ","policy_rationale":"\n   We aim to prevent potential offline harm that may be related to content on Facebook. While we understand that people commonly express disdain or disagreement by threatening or calling for violence in non-serious ways, we remove language that incites or facilitates serious violence. We remove content, disable accounts, and work with law enforcement when we believe there is a genuine risk of physical harm or direct threats to public safety. We also try to consider the language and context in order to distinguish casual statements from content that constitutes a credible threat to public or personal safety. In determining whether a threat is credible, we may also consider additional information like a person's public visibility and the risks to their physical safety. \n  \n     In some cases, we see aspirational or conditional threats directed at terrorists and other violent actors (e.g. Terrorists deserve to be killed), and we deem those non credible absent specific evidence to the contrary.  \n  \n "},"dangerous_individuals_organizations":{"other_content":"\n   \n  \n    We do not allow the following people (living or deceased) or groups to maintain a presence (for example, have an account, Page, Group) on our platform: \n    \nTerrorist organizations and terrorists, which include:\n   \n \n\t Any non-state actor that:\n  \t \n       Engages in, advocates, or lends substantial support to purposive and planned acts of violence, \n       Which causes or attempts to cause death, injury or serious harm to civilians, or any other person not taking direct part in the hostilities in a situation of armed conflict, and\/or significant damage to property linked to death, serious injury or serious harm to civilians \n    \t With the intent to coerce, intimidate and\/or influence a civilian population, government, or international organization \n       In order to achieve a political, religious, or ideological aim. \n     \n   \n \n \n     \n \nHate organizations and their leaders and prominent members     \n \n   A hate organization is defined as:\n  \t \n    \t Any association of three or more people that is organized under a name, sign, or symbol and that has an ideology, statements, or physical actions that attack individuals based on characteristics, including race, religious affiliation, nationality, ethnicity, gender, sex, sexual orientation, serious disease or disability. \n     \n     \n \n \n     \n Mass and multiple murderers (including attempts) \n\t \n     We consider a homicide to be a mass murder if it results in three or more deaths in one incident \n     We consider an attempted mass murder to be one where an individual uses a weapon or vehicle to attempt mass harm in a public space or against more than one person \n     We consider any individual who has committed two or more murders over multiple incidents or locations a multiple murderer \n    \n   \n \n     \n Human trafficking groups and their leaders\n\t \n     Human trafficking groups are organizations responsible for any of the following:\n    \t \n      \t Prostitution of others, forced\/bonded labor, slavery, or the removal of organs \n         Recruiting, transporting, transferring, detaining, providing, harboring, or receiving a minor, or an adult against their will \n       \n     \n   \n \n\n Criminal organizations and their leaders and prominent members\n\t \n     A criminal organization is defined as:\n    \t \n      \t Any association of three or more people that is united under a name, color(s), hand gesture(s) or recognized indicia, that has engaged in or threatens to engage in criminal activity, including (but not limited to)\n        \t \n          \t\t Homicide \n               Drug trafficking \n               Arms trafficking \n               Identity theft \n               Money laundering \n               Extortion or trafficking \n               Assault \n               Kidnapping \n             Sexual exploitation (covered in  section 7  and  section 8 ) \n           \n         \n       \n     \n   \n \n     \n      We do not allow symbols that represent any of the above organizations or individuals to be shared on our platform without context that condemns or neutrally discusses the content. \n     \n      We do not allow content that praises any of the above organizations or individuals or any acts committed by them. \n     \n      We do not allow coordination of support for any of the above organizations or individuals or any acts committed by them. \n      We do not allow content that praises, supports, or represents events that Facebook designates as terrorist attacks, hate crimes or mass shootings. \n    \n  \n ","policy_rationale":"\n   \nIn an effort to prevent and disrupt real-world harm, we do not allow any organizations or individuals that proclaim a violent mission or are engaged in violence to have a presence on Facebook. This includes organizations or individuals involved in the following:\n \n \n   Terrorist activity \n   Organized hate \n   Mass murder (including attempts) or multiple murder \n   Human trafficking \n   Organized violence or criminal activity \n   \n   \n     We also remove content that expresses support or praise for groups, leaders, or individuals involved in these activities. Learn more about our work to fight terrorism online  here . \n  \n "},"coordinating_harm_publicizing_crime":{"other_content":"\n   \n \n  \n    Do not post content that falls into the following categories: \n \n   Harm against people \n   \n    Statements of intent, calls to action, or advocating for harm against people that depicts, admits to, or promotes the following acts committed by you or your associates:\n \n   Acts of physical harm against humans, including acts of domestic violence, except when shared in a context of redemption or defense of self or another person \n   Swatting \n   Encouraging participation in a high risk viral challenge \n \n   \n   Harm against animals \n    \n     Statements of intent, calls to action, or advocating for harm against animals that depicts, admits to, or promotes:\n \n   Acts of physical harm against animals committed by you or your associates except in cases of hunting, fishing, religious sacrifice, food preparation or processing, pest or vermin, self-defense or redemption \n   Staged animal vs. animal fights, including acts committed by a third party \n \n   Harm against property \n   Statements of intent, calls to action, or advocating for harm against property that depicts, admits to, or promotes the following acts committed by you or your associates:\n  \n    Vandalism \n    Hacking when the intent is to hijack a domain, corrupt or disrupt cyber systems, seek ransoms, or gain unauthorized access to data systems \n    Theft when committed by you or your associates, as well as positive statements about theft when committed by a third party     \n  \n    \n   Voter and\/or Census Fraud  \n    \n \n   Offers to buy or sell votes with cash or gifts \n   Statements that advocate, provide instructions, or show explicit intent to illegally participate in a voting or census process \n  \n   \n     Voter and\/or Census Interference  \n  \n    Misrepresentation of the dates, locations, and times, and methods for voting or voter registration or census participation \n    Misrepresentation of who can vote, qualifications for voting, whether a vote will be counted, and what information and\/or materials must be provided in order to vote. \n    Misrepresentation of whether a candidate is running or not \n    Misrepresentation of who can participate in the census and what information or materials must be provided in order to participate \n    Calls for coordinated interference that would affect an individual\u2019s ability to participate in the census \n    Content stating that census or voting participation may or will result in law enforcement consequences (e.g., arrest, deportation, imprisonment) \n    Misrepresentation of government involvement in the census, including that an individual\u2019s census information will be shared with another government agency. \n    Other misrepresentations related to voting in an official election or census participation may be subject to false news standards, as referenced in  \n      section 20\n     \n \n  \n  \n \n  \n  \n    \n      For the following content, we include a label so that people are aware the content may be We also prohibit the purchase, sale, gifting, exchange, and transfer of firearms, including firearm parts or ammunition, between private individuals on Facebook. Some of these items are not regulated everywhere; however, because of the borderless nature of our community, we try to enforce our policies as consistently as possible. Firearm stores and online retailers may promote items available for sale off of our services as long as those retailers comply with all applicable laws and regulations. We allow discussions about sales of firearms and firearm parts in stores or by online retailers and advocating for changes to firearm regulation. content that encourages suicide or self-injury, including certain graphic imagery and real-time depictions that  experts tell us  might lead others to engage in similar behavior. Self-injury is defined as the intentional and direct injuring of the body, including self-mutilation and eating disorders. We want Facebook to be a space where people can share their experiences, raise awareness about these issues, and seek support from one another, which is why we allow people to discuss suicide and self-injury.\n    \n We work with organizations around the world to provide assistance to people in distress. We also talk to experts in suicide and self-injury to help inform our policies and enforcement. For example, we have been advised by experts that we should not remove live videos of self-injury while there is an opportunity for loved ones and authorities to provide help or resources. \n\n In against minors in a fight context shared with a condemning caption\n  \n  \n ","policy_rationale":"\n   Bullying and harassment happen in many places and come in many different forms, from making threats to releasing personally identifiable information, to sending threatening messages, and making unwanted malicious contact. We do not tolerate this kind of behavior because it prevents people from feeling safe and respected on Facebook. \n\n We distinguish between public figures and private individuals because we want to allow discussion, which often includes critical commentary of people who are featured in the news or who have a large public audience. For public figures, we remove attacks that are severe as well as certain attacks where the public figure is directly tagged in the post or comment. For private individuals, our protection goes further: we remove content that's meant to degrade or shame, including, for example, claims about someone's sexual activity. We recognize that bullying and harassment can have more of an emotional impact on minors, which is why our policies provide heightened protection for users between the ages of 13 and 18. \n\n Context and intent matter, and we allow people to share and re-share posts if it is clear that something was shared in order to condemn or draw attention to bullying and harassment. In certain instances, we require self-reporting because it helps us understand that the person targeted feels bullied or harassed. In addition to reporting such behavior and content, we encourage people to use  tools available on Facebook  to help protect against it. \n    \n     We also have a  Bullying Prevention Hub , which is a resource for teens, parents, and educators seeking support for issues related to bullying and other conflicts. It offers step-by-step guidance, including information on how to start important conversations about bullying. Learn more about what we\u2019re doing to protect people from bullying and harassment  here . \n   \n "},"human_exploitation":{"other_content":"\n   \n  \n    Do not post: \n    \n      Content or exhibit behavior that may lead to human exploitation, which includes any of the following:\n\n      \n        Sex Trafficking, covering minors and adults \n        The sale of children for illegal adoption\n         \n        Orphanage Trafficking and Orphanage Volun-tourism\n           \n        Forced Marriages\n         \n        Labor Exploitation (incl. bonded labor)\n         \n        Domestic Servitude\n         \n        Non-regenerative Organ Trafficking \n        Forced Criminal Activity (e.g. forced begging, forced drug trafficking) \n        Recruitment of Child Soldiers \n           \n\n      Content geared towards the:\n      \n        Recruitment of potential victims through force, fraud, coercion, enticement, deception, blackmail or other non-consensual acts. \n        Facilitation of human exploitation by coordinating, transporting, transferring, harboring or brokering of victims prior or during the exploitation.  \n        Exploitation of humans by promoting, depicting, or advocating for it. \n        \n      Content that offers or assists in smuggling of humans \n      \n         \n    \n ","policy_rationale":"\n   After consulting with outside experts from around the world, we are consolidating several existing exploitation policies that were previously housed in different sections of the Community Standards into one dedicated section that focuses on human exploitation and captures a broad range of harmful activities that may manifest on our platform. Experts think and talk about these issues under one umbrella \u2014 human exploitation.   \n     \n     \n     \n      In an effort to disrupt and prevent harm, we remove content that facilitates or coordinates the exploitation of humans, including human trafficking. We define human trafficking as the business of depriving someone of liberty for profit. It is the exploitation of humans in order to force them to engage   in commercial sex, labor, or other activities against their will. It relies on deception, force and coercion, and degrades humans by depriving them of their freedom while economically or materially benefiting others.   \n     \n     \n     \n      Human trafficking is multi-faceted and global; it can affect anyone regardless of age, socioeconomic background, ethnicity, gender, or location. It takes many forms, and any given trafficking situation can involve various stages of development. By the coercive nature of this abuse, victims cannot consent. \n     \n     \n     \n      While we need to be careful not to conflate human trafficking and smuggling, the two can be related and exhibit overlap. The United Nations defines human smuggling as the procurement or facilitation of illegal entry into a state across international borders. Without necessity for coercion or force, it may still result in the exploitation of vulnerable individuals who are trying to leave their country of origin, often in pursuit of a better life. Human smuggling is a crime against a state, relying on movement, and human trafficking is a crime against a person, relying on exploitation. \n \n their protected characteristic(s) with any of the following: \n        \n          Calls for segregation \n            Explicit Exclusion which includes but is not limited to \"expel\" or \"not allowed\".  \n           Political Exclusion defined as denial of right to political participation. \n          Economic Exclusion defined as denial of access to economic entitlements and limiting \n\n        We do allow criticism of immigration policies and arguments for restricting those policies. \n\n      Content that describes or negatively targets people with slurs, where slurs are defined as words commonly used as insulting labels for the above-listed characteristics. \n     \n\n    \n  \n ","policy_rationale":"\n   We do not allow hate speech on Facebook because it creates an environment of intimidation and exclusion and in some cases may promote real-world violence. \n\n     We define hate speech as a direct attack on people based on what we call protected characteristics \u2014 race, ethnicity, national origin, religious affiliation, sexual orientation, caste, sex, gender, gender identity, and serious disease or disability. We protect against attacks on the basis of age when age is paired with another protected characteristic, and also provide certain protections for immigration status. We define attack as violent or dehumanizing speech, statements of inferiority, or calls for exclusion or segregation. We separate attacks into three tiers of severity, as described below. \n\n     Sometimes people share content containing someone else\u2019s hate speech for the purpose of raising awareness or educating others. In some cases, words or terms that might otherwise violate our standards are used self-referentially or in an empowering way. People sometimes express contempt in the context of a romantic break-up. Other times, they use gender-exclusive language to control membership in a health or positive support group, such as a breastfeeding group for women only. In all of these cases, we allow the content but expect people to clearly indicate their intent, which helps us better understand why they shared it. Where the intention is unclear, we may remove the content. \n\n     We allow humor and social commentary related to these topics. In addition, we believe that people are more responsible when they share this kind of commentary using their authentic identity. \n\n     Click here to read our Hard Questions Blog  and learn more about our approach to hate speech. \n \n "},"graphic_violence":{"other_content":"\n   \n  \n    Do not post: \n    \n     \n Videos of people or dead bodies in non-medical settings if they depict\n   \n  \t Dismemberment \n     Visible internal organs; partially decomposed bodies \n     Charred or burning people unless in the context of cremation or self-immolation when that action is a form of political speech or newsworthy \n     Victims of cannibalism \n     Throat-slitting \n        \n \n      Live streams of capital punishment of a person \n      \n       Videos or photos that depict non-sexual child abuse, defined as\n   \n     Repeated kicking, beating, slapping, or stepping on by an adult or animal \n     Strangling or suffocating by an adult or animal \n     Drowning by an adult or animal \n     Biting through skin by an adult or animal \n     Poisoning by an adult \n     Forcible restraint by an adult \n     Inflicting of burn or cut wounds by an adult \n     Forcible smoking \n Tossing, rotating, or shaking of an infant (too young to stand) by their wrists\/ankles, arms\/legs, or neck \n   \n      \n\n     \n    \n  \n   \n      \n  For the following content, we include a warning screen so that people are aware the content may be disturbing. Restrictions on the display of sexual activity also apply to digitally created content unless it is posted for educational, humorous, or satirical purposes. \n\n     Our nudity policies have become more nuanced over time. We understand that nudity can be shared for a variety of reasons, including as a form of protest, to raise awareness about a cause, or for educational or medical reasons. For example, while we restrict some images of female breasts that include the nipple, we allow other images, including those depicting acts of protest, women actively engaged in breast-feeding, and photos of post-mastectomy scarring. \u201d) \n       Failing to direct to promised content (e.g., \u201c Click here for a discount code at Nordstrom \u201d;  false play buttons ) \n       Directing users off of Facebook through the deceptive or misleading use of URLs, defined as:\n         \n           Cloaking:  Presenting different content to Facebook users and Facebook crawlers or tools. \n           Misleading content : Content contains a link that promises one type of content but delivers something substantially different. \n           Deceptive Pop-up websites : Websites that require an action (captcha, watch ad, click here) in order to view the expected landing page content and the domain name of the URL changes after the required action is complete.  \n           Like \/ Share-Gating:  Landing pages that require users to like, share, or otherwise engage with content before gaining access to off-Facebook content. \n           Deceptive Landing Page Functionality:  Websites that have a misleading user interface, which results in accidental traffic being generated (pop-ups\/unders, clickjacking, etc.) \n           Impersonation:  The website pretends to be a reputable brand or service by using a name, domain, or content featuring typos, misspellings, or other means to impersonate well-known brands www.faceb00k.com, www.face_book.com, using a landing page similar to another, trusted site to mislead visitors).  \n           And other behaviors that are substantially similar to those listed above. \n         \n          \n\n    \n  \n ","policy_rationale":"\n   We work hard to limit the spread of spam because we do not want to allow content that is designed to deceive, or that attempts to mislead users to increase viewership. This content creates a negative user experience and detracts from people's ability to engage authentically in online communities. We also aim to prevent people from abusing our platform, products, or features to artificially increase viewership or distribute content  en masse  for commercial gain. \n "},"cybersecurity":{"other_content":"\n   \n  \n    Do not: \n    \n      Attempt to compromise user accounts or gather sensitive information through unauthorized means, defined as: \n \n   Gaining access to any account or user data other than your own without explicit permission from the account owner. \n   Encouraging or deceiving users and entities to download or run files or programs that will compromise a user\u2019s online or data security. Such files and programs will be deemed malicious software or \"malware\" if they harm or gain unauthorized access to a computer, device, or network. \n   Acquiring or requesting another user\u2019s login credentials, whether explicitly or through deceptive means such as phishing (e.g. fake surveys designed to capture log-in info or links to fake login pages or impostor websites). \n   Attempting to obtain the sensitive information of others such as usernames, passwords, or other personal information, through deceptive means or the use of malicious software or websites.  \n   Publicly sharing your own or others\u2019 login information on platform or through a third party service.  \n   Creating, sharing, or hosting malicious software or malicious browser extensions to compromise accounts or gain access to user data. \n   Providing online infrastructure, including Web Hosting Services, Domain Name System servers, and ad networks that enables abusive links such that a majority of those links on Facebook or Instagram violate the Spam or Cybersecurity sections of the Community Standards.  \n      \n          \n\n    \n  \n ","policy_rationale":"\n   We recognize that the safety of our users extends to the security of their personal information. Attempts to gather sensitive personal information by deceptive or invasive methods are harmful to the authentic, open, and safe atmosphere that we want to foster. Therefore, we do not allow attempts to gather sensitive user information through the abuse of our platform and products.\n \n "},"inauthentic_behavior":{"other_content":"\n   \n  \n    Do not: \n    \n      \n      \n        Use multiple Facebook accounts or share accounts between multiple people \n        Misuse Facebook or Instagram reporting systems to harass others \n        Conceal a Page\u2019s purpose by misleading users about the ownership or control of that Page \n        Engage in or claim to engage in Inauthentic Behavior, which is defined as the use of Facebook or Instagram assets (accounts, pages, groups, or events), to mislead people or Facebook: \n       \t \n           about the identity, purpose, or origin of the entity that they represent  \n           about the popularity of Facebook or Instagram content or assets \n           about the purpose of an audience or community \n           about the source or origin of content \n           to evade enforcement under our Community Standards \n         \n        \n        Engage in, or claim to engage in Coordinated Inauthentic Behavior, defined as the use of multiple Facebook or Instagram assets, working in concert to engage in Inauthentic Behavior (as defined above), where the use of fake accounts is central to the operation \n        Engage in or claim to engage in Foreign or Government Interference, which is Coordinated Inauthentic Behavior conducted on behalf of a foreign or government actor. \n      \n      \n    \n  \n ","policy_rationale":"\n   In line with our commitment to authenticity, we don't allow people to misrepresent themselves on Facebook, use fake accounts, artificially boost the popularity of content, or engage in behaviors designed to enable other violations under our Community Standards. This policy is intended to create a space where people can trust the people and communities they interact with. \n "},"false_news":{"other_content":"\n   \n  \n    We are working to build a more informed community and reduce the spread of false news in a number of different ways, namely by \n    \n     \t \n         Disrupting economic incentives for people, Pages, and domains that propagate misinformation  \n         Using various signals, including feedback from our community, to inform a machine learning model that predicts which stories may be false \n         Reducing the distribution of content rated as false by independent third-party fact-checkers \n         Empowering people to decide for themselves what to read, trust, and share by informing them with more context and promoting news literacy \n         Collaborating with academics and other organizations to help solve this challenging issue \n       \n    \n  \n ","policy_rationale":"\n   Reducing the spread of false news on Facebook is a responsibility that we take seriously. We also recognize that this is a challenging and sensitive issue. We want to help people stay informed without stifling productive public discourse. There is also a fine line between false news and satire or opinion. For these reasons, we don't remove false news from Facebook but instead, significantly reduce its distribution by showing it lower in the News Feed. Learn more about our work to reduce the spread of false news  here . \n "},"manipulated_media":{"other_content":"\n   \n \n    Do not post: \n    \n     \t \n         Video\n         \n         that has been edited or synthesized, beyond adjustments for clarity or quality, in ways that are not apparent to an average person, and would likely mislead an average person to believe that a subject of the video said words that they did not say AND \n           is the product of artificial intelligence or machine learning, including deep learning techniques (e.g., a technical deepfake), that merges, combines, replaces, and\/or superimposes content onto a video, creating a video that appears authentic. \n      \n           This policy does not extend to content that is parody or satire or is edited to omit words that were said or change the order of words that were said.\n        \n    \n  \n ","policy_rationale":"\n   Media, including image, audio, or video, can be edited in a variety of ways. In many cases, these changes are benign, like a filter effect on a photo. In other cases, the manipulation isn\u2019t apparent and could mislead, particularly in the case of video content. We aim to remove this category of manipulated media when the criteria laid out below have been met. \n     In addition, we will continue to invest in partnerships (including with journalists, academics and independent fact-checkers) to help us reduce the distribution of false news and misinformation, as well as to better inform people about the content they encounter online.  \n \n "},"memorialization":{"other_content":"\n   \n  \n    For victims of murder and suicide we will remove the following content if it appears on the deceased\u2019s profile photo, cover photo, or among recent timeline posts when requested by a legacy contact or family member of the deceased: \n\n\n     \n      \n          \n      Visual depiction of the object used in the deceased\u2019s death \n      Imagery of the convicted or alleged murderer of the deceased \n             Content related to the deceased\u2019s death \n       \n      \nFor victims of murder, we will also remove the convicted or alleged murderer from the deceased\u2019s profile if referenced in relationship status or among friends. \n       When we have additional context provided by the legacy contact or a family member of the deceased, we may:\n \n      \n       Remove bullying or harassment violations on a memorialized profile, which normally require the individual to self-report \n\n   Remove praise or support for the death, disease, or harm of the deceased person on a memorialized profile \n\n\n   Change the deceased\u2019s individual\u2019s privacy settings from public to friends-only when there is harmful content on the profile  \n\n   Change a violating account name on the profile of the deceased individual \n \n     \n         \n    \n ","policy_rationale":"\n   When someone passes away, friends and family can request that we  memorialize  the Facebook account. Once memorialized, the word \"Remembering\" appears above the name on the person's profile to help make it that the account is now a memorial site and protects against attempted logins and fraudulent activity. To respect the choices someone made while  alive, we aim to preserve their account after they pass away. We have also made it possible for people to identify a  legacy contact  to look after their account after they pass away. To support the bereaved, in some instances we may remove or change certain content when the legacy contact or family members request it.\n     Visit  Hard Questions  for more information about our memorialization policy and process. And see our  Newsroom  for the latest tools we're building to support people during these difficult times. \n "},"intellectual_property":{"other_content":"\n   \n  \n    Upon receipt of a report from a rights holder or an authorized representative, we will remove or restrict content that engages in: \n    \n \n   Copyright infringement    \n   Trademark infringement \n \n    \n  \n ","policy_rationale":"\n   Facebook takes  intellectual property rights  seriously and believes they are important to promoting expression, creativity, and innovation in our community. You own all of the content and information you post on Facebook, and you control how it is shared through your privacy and application settings. However, before sharing content on Facebook, please be sure you have the right to do so. We ask that you respect other people\u2019s copyrights, trademarks, and other legal rights. We are committed to helping people and organizations promote and protect their intellectual property rights. Facebook\u2019s  Terms of Service  do not allow people to post content that violates someone else\u2019s intellectual property rights, including copyright and trademark. We are a service for more than two billion people to freely express themselves across countries and cultures and in dozens of languages. \n     We recognize how important it is for Facebook to be a place where people feel empowered to communicate, and we take seriously our role in keeping abuse off our service. That\u2019s why we\u2019ve  developed a set of Community Standards  that outline what is and is not allowed on Facebook. Our policies are based on feedback from our community and the advice of experts in fields such as technology, public safety and human rights. To ensure that everyone\u2019s voice is valued, we take great care to craft policies that are inclusive of different views and beliefs, in particular those of people and communities that might otherwise be overlooked or marginalized. \n   \n         \n     REITERATING OUR COMMITMENT TO VOICE \n     The goal of our Community Standards has always been to  create a place for expression and give people a voice . This has not and will not change. Building community and bringing the world closer together depends on people\u2019s ability to share diverse views, experiences, ideas and information. We want people to be able to talk openly about the issues that matter to them, even if some may disagree or find them objectionable. In some cases, we allow content which would otherwise go against our Community Standards \u2013 if it is newsworthy and in the public interest. We do this only after weighing the public interest value against the risk of harm and we look to international human rights standards to make these judgments.  \n    \n     Our commitment to expression is paramount, but we recognize the internet creates new and increased opportunities for abuse. For these reasons, when we limit expression, we do it in service of one or more the following values: \n   \n       \n\n     Authenticity:  We want to make sure the content people are seeing on Facebook is authentic. We believe that authenticity creates a better environment for sharing, and that\u2019s why we don\u2019t want people using Facebook to misrepresent who they are or what they\u2019re doing.\n \n    \n    \n      \n    \n     Safety:  We are committed to making Facebook a safe place. Expression that threatens people has the potential to intimidate, exclude or silence others and isn\u2019t allowed on Facebook. \n  \n    \n  \n    \n    \n     Privacy:  We are committed to protecting personal privacy and information. Privacy gives people the freedom to be themselves, and to choose how and when to share on Facebook and to connect more easily.\n \n        \n  \n    \n     Dignity:  We believe that all people are equal in dignity and rights. We expect that people will respect the dignity of others and not harass or degrade others. \n    \n\n\n    \n    \n     Our Community Standards apply to everyone, all around the world, and to all types of content. They\u2019re designed to be comprehensive \u2013 for example, content that might not be considered hateful may still be removed for violating a different policy. We recognize that words mean different things or affect people differently depending on their local community, language, or background. We work hard to account for these nuances while also applying our policies consistently and fairly to people and their expression. In the case of certain policies, we require more information and\/or context to enforce in line with our Community Standards. \n\n     People can report potentially violating content, including Pages, Groups, Profiles, individual content, and comments. We also give people control over their own experience by allowing them to\n       block ,   unfollow \n       or \n        hide  people and posts.\n       \n\n     The consequences for violating our Community Standards vary depending on the severity of the violation and the person's history on the platform. For instance, we may warn someone for a first violation, but if they continue to violate our policies, we may restrict their ability to post on Facebook or disable their profile. We also may notify law enforcement when we believe there is a genuine risk of physical harm or a direct threat to public safety. \n     Our Community Standards are a guide for what is and isn\u2019t allowed on Facebook. It is in this spirit that we ask members of the Facebook community to follow these guidelines. \n     \nPlease note that the English version of the Community Standards reflects the most up to date set of the policies and should be used as the master document. \n   \n   \n  \n    Ne publiez pas\u00a0: \n    \n  Des menaces pouvant entra\u00eener la mort des cibles (et toute autre forme de violence tr\u00e8s grave), lorsqu\u2019une menace se d\u00e9finit comme suit\u00a0:\n\n      \n              des d\u00e9clarations d\u2019intention de commettre des actes de violence meurtri\u00e8re\u00a0; ou \n        des incitations \u00e0 des actes de violence graves, y compris du contenu sans cible identifi\u00e9e, mais repr\u00e9sent\u00e9e par un symbole ou avec l\u2019image d\u2019un armement exprimant de la violence\u00a0; ou \n        des d\u00e9clarations d\u2019incitation \u00e0 des actes de violence graves\u00a0; ou \n        des d\u00e9clarations conditionnelles ou de souhait de commettre un acte de violence grave \n     \n      \n      Le contenu r\u00e9clamant ou offrant des services pour tuer (par exemple, des tueurs \u00e0 gages, des mercenaires ou des assassins) ou pr\u00e9conise le recours \u00e0 un tueur \u00e0 gages, un mercenaire ou un assassin contre la cible. \n     \n      L\u2019admission de la volont\u00e9, la d\u00e9claration de l\u2019intention ou de soutien \u00e0 une intention, l\u2019appel \u00e0 l\u2019action ou la d\u00e9claration conditionnelle ou le souhait de kidnapper une cible. \n     \n   Des menaces entra\u00eenant des blessures graves (violence de gravit\u00e9 moyenne) pour des personnes priv\u00e9es, des personnalit\u00e9s publiques mineures ou des personnes ou des groupes \u00e0 risque, lorsqu\u2019une menace se d\u00e9finit comme suit\u00a0:\n\n      \n des d\u00e9clarations d\u2019intention de commettre des actes de violence\u00a0; ou \n        des d\u00e9clarations d\u2019incitation \u00e0 la violence\u00a0; ou \n        des appels \u00e0 la violence de gravit\u00e9 moyenne, y compris le contenu n\u2019identifiant pas la cible, mais la repr\u00e9sentant par un symbole\u00a0; ou \n        des d\u00e9clarations conditionnelles ou de souhait de commettre un acte de violence\u00a0; ou  \n   du contenu d\u00e9signant d\u2019autres cibles, except\u00e9 les personnes priv\u00e9es, les personnalit\u00e9s publiques mineures, les personnes ou groupes \u00e0 risque et toute autre cible cr\u00e9dible\u00a0: \n          des d\u00e9clarations d\u2019intention de commettre des actes de violence\u00a0; ou \n          des appels aux actes de violence\u00a0; ou \n          des d\u00e9clarations d\u2019incitation \u00e0 la violence\u00a0; ou \n       des d\u00e9clarations conditionnelles ou de souhait de commettre un acte de violence \n   \n    \n\n      Des menaces entra\u00eenant des blessures physiques (ou toute autre forme de violence de faible gravit\u00e9) pour des personnes priv\u00e9es (signalement requis de leur part) ou des personnalit\u00e9s publiques mineures comprenant\u00a0: \n                des d\u00e9clarations d\u2019intention, des appels aux actes, des incitations, des d\u00e9clarations conditionnelles ou exprimant le souhait de commettre ","policy_rationale":"\n   Nous souhaitons emp\u00eacher tout risque de danger hors ligne potentiellement li\u00e9 \u00e0 du contenu sur Facebook. Bien qu\u2019il soit commun pour des utilisateurs d\u2019exprimer leur d\u00e9dain ou leur d\u00e9saccord sous forme de menaces ou d\u2019appels \u00e0 la violence, mais de mani\u00e8re non s\u00e9rieuse, nous supprimons les propos qui encouragent ou permettent des violences graves. Lorsque nous pensons qu\u2019un contenu repr\u00e9sente un r\u00e9el risque de pr\u00e9judice physique ou une atteinte directe \u00e0 la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 publique, nous supprimons le contenu, d\u00e9sactivons les comptes concern\u00e9s et collaborons avec les autorit\u00e9s. Nous essayons \u00e9galement d\u2019examiner le langage utilis\u00e9 et le contexte pour distinguer les d\u00e9clarations triviales de celles qui repr\u00e9sentent une menace r\u00e9elle pour la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 publique ou celle d\u2019un individu. Pour d\u00e9terminer la cr\u00e9dibilit\u00e9 d\u2019une menace, nous examinons \u00e9ventuellement d\u2019autres informations, telles que le degr\u00e9 d\u2019exposition publique d\u2019un individu et les risques pour sa s\u00e9curit\u00e9 physique. \n  \n     Dans certains cas, nous voyons des aspirations et des d\u00e9clarations conditionnelles de violence contre des terroristes ou d\u2019autres auteurs d\u2019actes violents (par exemple\u00a0: les terroristes m\u00e9ritent la mort), et nous ne les jugeons pas cr\u00e9dibles en l\u2019absence de preuves sp\u00e9cifiques du contraire.  \n  \n "},"dangerous_individuals_organizations":{"other_content":"\n   \n  \n    Nous n\u2019autorisons pas les individus (vivants ou d\u00e9c\u00e9d\u00e9s) et groupes suivants \u00e0 une ran\u00e7on ou obtenir des acc\u00e8s non autoris\u00e9s \u00e0 des syst\u00e8mes de donn\u00e9es \n    Vol lorsqu\u2019il est commis par vous ou vos associ\u00e9s ainsi que les d\u00e9clarations \n   D\u00e9clarations qui donnent l\u2019instruction, montrent une intention explicite de participer ill\u00e9galement \u00e0 un vote ou un recensement ou incitent \u00e0 le faire \n  \n   \n     Ing\u00e9rence \u00e9lectorale et ing\u00e9rence dans un recensement  \n  \n    Fausses d\u00e9clarations sur les dates, lieux et heures ainsi que les m\u00e9thodes de vote ou d\u2019inscription sur les listes \u00e9lectorales ou au recensement \n    Fausses d\u00e9clarations sur les personnes qui peuvent voter, les qualifications requises pour voter, la question de savoir si un vote sera compt\u00e9 et quels renseignements et\/ou documents doivent \u00eatre fournis pour pouvoir voter. \n    Fausses d\u00e9clarations sur la (non-) participation d\u2019un candidat \n    Fausses r\u00e9sulter ou r\u00e9sultera en des cons\u00e9quences l\u00e9gales (par exemple l\u2019arr\u00eat, l\u2019expulsion, l\u2019emprisonnement) \n    Fausses d\u00e9clarations sur l\u2019implication du Certains de ces articles ne sont pas r\u00e9glement\u00e9s partout\u00a0; toutefois, en raison de la nature sans fronti\u00e8res de notre communaut\u00e9, nous essayons d\u2019appliquer nos r\u00e8glements de la mani\u00e8re la plus coh\u00e9rente possible. Les armureries et les vendeurs en ligne peuvent faire la promotion d\u2019articles disponibles \u00e0 la vente en dehors de nos services tant qu'ils sont conformes aux lois et r\u00e9glementations en vigueur. Nous autorisons les discussions concernant la vente d\u2019armes \u00e0 feu et de pi\u00e8ces d\u2019armes \u00e0 feu dans les boutiques ou par les vendeurs en ligne et pr\u00f4nant le changement de la r\u00e9glementation sur les armes \u00e0 feu. de promouvoir un environnement s\u00fbr sur Facebook, nous supprimons tout contenu qui encourage le suicide ou l\u2019automutilation, y compris certaines images explicites et repr\u00e9sentations en temps r\u00e9el qui,  selon les experts , pourraient inciter d\u2019autres personnes \u00e0 adopter un comportement similaire. Nous souhaitons faire de Facebook un espace o\u00f9 chacun peut partager ses exp\u00e9riences, sensibiliser sur ces fl\u00e9aux et rechercher un soutien mutuel. C\u2019est pour cela que nous autorisons les discussions sur le suicide et l\u2019automutilation.\n    \n Nous travaillons avec des organisations du monde entier afin de fournir une assistance aux personnes en d\u00e9tresse. d\u2019attirer l\u2019attention sur la violence et l\u2019exploitation sexuelles. Nous pensons qu\u2019il s\u2019agit d\u2019un \u00e9l\u00e9ment important pour d\u00e9velopper une conscience collective et fonder une communaut\u00e9. Afin de cr\u00e9er un espace pour cette conversation tout en favorisant un environnement s\u00fbr, nous supprimons tout contenu qui menace de violence, de harc\u00e8lement ou d\u2019exploitation sexuelle, ou d\u00e9crit ou encourage ces pratiques, tout en proposant un espace o\u00f9 les victimes peuvent partager leur exp\u00e9rience. Nous supprimons le contenu qui affiche, pr\u00e9conise ou coordonne des actes sexuels avec des parties non consentantes ou des services sexuels commerciaux, tels que la prostitution et les services d\u2019escorte. Ce faisant, nous \u00e9vitons de favoriser des transactions pouvant impliquer des actes sexuels dans le cadre d\u2019un trafic, sous la contrainte et non consentis.\n\n     Pour prot\u00e9ger les victimes et les survivants, nous supprimons \u00e9galement les images relatant des incidents de violence sexuelle et les images intimes partag\u00e9es sans l\u2019autorisation des personnes repr\u00e9sent\u00e9es.  \n  \n ","policy_rationale":"\n   Le harc\u00e8lement et l\u2019intimidation se produisent en divers lieux et sous diff\u00e9rentes formes, qu\u2019il s\u2019agisse d\u2019une menace de diffusion d\u2019informations personnelles identifiables, de l\u2019envoi de messages de menace ou de contacts malveillants ind\u00e9sir\u00e9s. Nous ne tol\u00e9rons pas ce type de comportement, car il emp\u00eache les gens de se sentir respect\u00e9s et en s\u00e9curit\u00e9 sur Facebook. \n\n Nous distinguons les personnalit\u00e9s publiques des personnes priv\u00e9es, car notre plate-forme pr\u00f4ne l\u2019\u00e9change, ce qui implique souvent des commentaires critiques concernant des individus qui attirent l\u2019attention des m\u00e9dias ou du grand public. Concernant les personnalit\u00e9s publiques, nous supprimons les attaques graves et certaines attaques qui identifient directement la personnalit\u00e9 publique dans une publication ou un commentaire. Concernant les personnes priv\u00e9es, notre protection est plus large\u00a0: nous supprimons le contenu visant \u00e0 rabaisser une personne ou \u00e0 la couvrir de honte, et, notamment, les d\u00e9clarations relatives aux activit\u00e9s sexuelles de quelqu\u2019un. Nous reconnaissons que l\u2019intimidation et le harc\u00e8lement peuvent avoir des r\u00e9percussions \u00e9motionnelles plus graves pour les mineurs. C\u2019est pourquoi nos politiques offrent une protection plus \u00e9lev\u00e9e pour les utilisateurs \u00e2g\u00e9s de 13\u00a0\u00e0 18\u00a0ans. \n\n Le contexte et l\u2019intention importent\u00a0; nous autorisons les personnes \u00e0 partager et \u00e0 repartager des publications si le contenu partag\u00e9 vise clairement \u00e0 condamner l\u2019intimidation et le harc\u00e8lement ou \u00e0 attirer l\u2019attention sur ces comportements. Dans certains cas, nous demandons que la personne cibl\u00e9e fasse elle-m\u00eame le signalement, car cela nous permet de savoir qu\u2019elle se sent intimid\u00e9e et harcel\u00e9e. En plus de signaler de tels comportements et contenus, nous encourageons les gens \u00e0 utiliser  les outils disponibles sur Facebook  pour se prot\u00e9ger contre ceux-ci. \n    \n     Nous avons \u00e9galement une  plate-forme de pr\u00e9vention contre l\u2019intimidation , qui est une ressource destin\u00e9e aux adolescents, aux parents et aux \u00e9ducateurs cherchant un soutien pour les questions li\u00e9es \u00e0 l\u2019intimidation et \u00e0 d\u2019autres conflits. Elle offre des conseils pas \u00e0 pas, y compris des informations sur la mani\u00e8re d\u2019ouvrir des discussions importantes concernant l\u2019intimidation. Apprenez-en davantage sur les mesures que nous prenons pour prot\u00e9ger les gens contre le harc\u00e8lement et l\u2019intimidation  ici . \n   \n "},"human_exploitation":{"other_content":"\n   \n  \n    Ne publiez pas\u00a0: \n    \n      Du contenu (ou n\u2019adoptez pas de comportement) pouvant conduire \u00e0 l\u2019exploitation des personnes, notamment sous les formes suivantes\u00a0:\n\n      \n        Exploitation sexuelle des mineurs et des adultes \n        Vente d\u2019enfants \u00e0 des fins d\u2019adoption ill\u00e9gale\n         \n        Exploitation dans des orphelinats et tourisme de volontariat dans des orphelinats \n        Mariages forc\u00e9s\n         \n        Travail forc\u00e9 (y compris travail asservi)\n         \n        Servitude domestique\n         \n        Trafic d\u2019organes ne se r\u00e9g\u00e9n\u00e9rant pas \n        Activit\u00e9s criminelles forc\u00e9es (par ex.\u00a0: mendicit\u00e9 forc\u00e9e, trafic de drogue forc\u00e9) \n        Recrutement d\u2019enfants soldats \n           \n\n      Du contenu favorisant\u00a0:\n      \n        Le recrutement de victimes potentielles par la force, la fraude, la contrainte, la sollicitation, la tromperie, le chantage ou autres actes non consentis \n        La contribution \u00e0 l\u2019exploitation des personnes en organisant, transportant, transf\u00e9rant, dissimulant ou n\u00e9gociant des victimes avant ou pendant leur exploitation  \n        L\u2019exploitant des humains en glorifiant, d\u00e9peignant ou pr\u00f4nant sa pratique \n        \n      Du contenu proposant d\u2019assurer le passage clandestin de personnes ou d\u2019y contribuer \n      \n         \n    \n ","policy_rationale":"\n   Apr\u00e8s avoir consult\u00e9 des sp\u00e9cialistes externes du monde entier, nous r\u00e9unissons plusieurs politiques concernant l\u2019exploitation, qui \u00e9taient jusqu\u2019\u00e0 pr\u00e9sent r\u00e9parties dans diff\u00e9rentes sections des Standards de la communaut\u00e9, pour n\u2019en former qu\u2019une\u00a0: elle sera centr\u00e9e sur l\u2019exploitation des personnes et abordera un grand nombre de pratiques n\u00e9fastes pouvant se manifester sur notre plate-forme. Ces sp\u00e9cialistes regroupent ces probl\u00e9matiques sous une appellation commune\u00a0: l\u2019exploitation des personnes.   \n     \n     \n     \n      Pour emp\u00eacher et r\u00e9duire ces pratiques, nous supprimons le contenu qui contribue \u00e0 l\u2019exploitation des personnes ou la coordonne, notamment la traite des personnes. Nous d\u00e9finissons la traite des personnes comme une activit\u00e9 privant un individu de sa libert\u00e9 pour en tirer profit. Il s\u2019agit d\u2019exploiter une personne pour la contraindre \u00e0 la    prostitution, au travail forc\u00e9 ou \u00e0 d\u2019autres activit\u00e9s contre son gr\u00e9. Elle fonctionne par la tromperie, la force et la contrainte, et avilit les individus en les privant de leur libert\u00e9 pour le profit \u00e9conomique ou mat\u00e9riel d\u2019autres personnes.   \n     \n     \n     \n      La traite des personnes touche le monde entier et prend de nombreuses formes\u00a0; elle peut toucher tous les humains, quels que soient leur \u00e2ge, leurs origines socio\u00e9conomiques, leur ethnie, leur genre et leur lieu de vie. Elle prend de nombreux visages, et tous les types de traite peuvent prendre diff\u00e9rentes ampleurs. En raison de la nature contraignante de cette maltraitance, les victimes ne sont pas consentantes. \n     \n     \n     \n      Bien que nous prenions soin de faire la distinction entre traite des personnes et passage clandestin, ces deux pratiques peuvent \u00eatre associ\u00e9es et se recouper. Les Nations Unies d\u00e9finissent le passage clandestin des personnes comme le fait de permettre ou d\u2019assurer l\u2019entr\u00e9e ill\u00e9gale dans un pays en traversant une fronti\u00e8re internationale. Sans qu\u2019il soit fait appel \u00e0 la contrainte ou \u00e0 la force, il peut tout de m\u00eame aboutir \u00e0 l\u2019exploitation de personnes vuln\u00e9rables qui tentent de quitter leur pays d\u2019origine en qu\u00eate d\u2019une vie meilleure. Le passage clandestin de personnes est un crime contre un \u00e9tat reposant sur un mouvement, tandis que la traite des personnes est un crime contre un individu reposant sur une exploitation. \n \n confidentialit\u00e9 et \u00e0 la protection des informations personnelles de nos utilisateurs. Nous travaillons sans rel\u00e2che pour s\u00e9curiser votre compte et prot\u00e9ger vos informations personnelles en vue d\u2019\u00e9viter tout dommage physique ou financier \u00e9ventuel. ou de d\u00e9clarations sur le comportement se rapportant \u00e0\u00a0:\n       \t \n           Des insectes \n           Des animaux culturellement per\u00e7us dans une culture comme inf\u00e9rieurs sur des personnes fond\u00e9e sur ce que nous appelons des caract\u00e9ristiques prot\u00e9g\u00e9es\u00a0: l\u2019origine ethnique, l\u2019origine nationale, la religion, l\u2019orientation sexuelle, la caste, le sexe, le genre, l\u2019identit\u00e9 sexuelle, et les maladies graves ou les handicaps. Nous prot\u00e9geons des attaques bas\u00e9es sur l\u2019\u00e2ge lorsque l\u2019\u00e2ge est associ\u00e9 \u00e0 une autre caract\u00e9ristique prot\u00e9g\u00e9e et nous fournissons \u00e9galement certaines protections pour le statut d\u2019immigration. Nous d\u00e9finissons une attaque comme un discours violent ou d\u00e9shumanisant, une affirmation d\u2019inf\u00e9riorit\u00e9, ou un appel \u00e0 l\u2019exclusion ou \u00e0 la s\u00e9gr\u00e9gation. nudit\u00e9 et d\u2019activit\u00e9s sexuelles, car certaines personnes au sein de notre communaut\u00e9 peuvent \u00eatre sensibles \u00e0 ce type de contenu. En outre, nous supprimons par d\u00e9faut les images de nature sexuelle pour emp\u00eacher le partage de contenus montrant des actes non consentis ou des mineurs. Les restrictions sur l\u2019affichage d\u2019activit\u00e9 sexuelle s\u2019appliquent \u00e9galement au contenu cr\u00e9\u00e9 num\u00e9riquement, sauf si le contenu est publi\u00e9 \u00e0 des fins p\u00e9dagogiques, humoristiques ou satiriques. \n\n     Avec le temps, nous avons adapt\u00e9 nos r\u00e8glements relatifs \u00e0 la nudit\u00e9. Nous comprenons que les contenus montrant des sc\u00e8nes de nudit\u00e9 peuvent \u00eatre partag\u00e9s pour diverses raisons, notamment dans le cadre d\u2019une protestation, pour sensibiliser \u00e0 une cause, ou \u00e0 des fins p\u00e9dagogiques ou sanitaires. Par cons\u00e9quent, nous acceptons les contenus respectant de tels motifs. Par exemple, alors que nous limitons certaines images de la poitrine f\u00e9minine qui montrent le mamelon, nous autorisons d\u2019autres types d\u2019images, notamment celles illustrant des actes de protestation, des femmes d\u00e9fendant activement l\u2019allaitement ou des cicatrices de mastectomie. Nous reconnaissons \u00e9galement qu\u2019il s\u2019agit d\u2019un probl\u00e8me \u00e9pineux et d\u00e9licat. Nous voulons que les gens restent inform\u00e9s sans \u00e9touffer les d\u00e9bats publics productifs. En outre, il n\u2019y a qu\u2019un pas entre les fausses informations et la satire ou les avis personnels. Pour ces raisons, nous ne supprimons pas les fausses informations de Facebook, mais en limitons significativement la diffusion en les affichant plus bas dans le fil d\u2019actualit\u00e9. Notre service permet \u00e0 plus de deux\u00a0milliards de personnes de s\u2019exprimer librement, au-del\u00e0 des fronti\u00e8res et des cultures, dans des dizaines de langues. \n     Nous sommes conscients de l\u2019importance pour Facebook d\u2019offrir un espace incitant les gens \u00e0 communiquer, et nous prenons tr\u00e8s au s\u00e9rieux notre r\u00f4le afin d\u2019\u00e9carter les abus de notre service. C\u2019est la raison pour laquelle nous avons  cr\u00e9\u00e9 un ensemble de Standards de la communaut\u00e9  qui expliquent ce qui est autoris\u00e9, ou non, sur Facebook. Nos politiques sont fond\u00e9es sur les retours de notre communaut\u00e9 et l\u2019avis de sp\u00e9cialistes dans des domaines comme les technologies, la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 publique et les droits de l\u2019homme. Pour nous assurer que tout le monde est respect\u00e9, nous nous effor\u00e7ons de cr\u00e9er des politiques qui prennent en compte les diff\u00e9rents points de vue et croyances, surtout ceux des personnes et communaut\u00e9s marginalis\u00e9es ou n\u00e9glig\u00e9es. \n   \n         \n     R\u00c9IT\u00c9RER NOTRE ENGAGEMENT POUR L\u2019EXPRESSION \n     L\u2019objectif de nos Standards de la communaut\u00e9 a toujours \u00e9t\u00e9 de  cr\u00e9er un espace d\u2019expression et de donner une voix aux personnes . Cela n\u2019a pas chang\u00e9 et cela ne changera pas. Pour cr\u00e9er des communaut\u00e9s et rapprocher les gens, il faut pouvoir partager des points de vue, des exp\u00e9riences, des id\u00e9es et des informations vari\u00e9s. Nous voulons que les personnes puissent s\u2019exprimer ouvertement sur les sujets qui comptent pour elles, m\u00eame si d\u2019autres peuvent ne pas \u00eatre d\u2019accord ou trouver ces sujets d\u00e9sagr\u00e9ables. Dans certains cas, nous autorisons la publication de contenu qui va \u00e0 l\u2019encontre de nos Standards de la communaut\u00e9 s\u2019il est pertinent et d\u2019int\u00e9r\u00eat public. Nous prenons cette d\u00e9cision en \u00e9valuant l\u2019impact positif pour l\u2019int\u00e9r\u00eat public par rapport \u00e0 la nuisance potentielle, et nous nous appuyons sur les principes universels des droits de l\u2019homme.  \n    \n     La possibilit\u00e9 de s\u2019exprimer est notre priorit\u00e9, mais nous sommes conscients qu\u2019Internet est une source de formes d\u2019abus nouvelles et croissantes. Aussi, lorsque nous limitons l\u2019expression, nous le faisons pour le respect d\u2019une ou de plusieurs des valeurs suivantes\u00a0: \n   \n       \n\n     Authenticit\u00e9\u00a0:  Nous voulons nous assurer que le contenu que les personnes voient sur Facebook est authentique. Nous sommes convaincus que l\u2019authenticit\u00e9 cr\u00e9e un meilleur environnement pour le partage, et nous ne voulons donc pas que les personnes qui utilisent Facebook mentent sur leur identit\u00e9 ou leurs activit\u00e9s.\n  S\u00e9curit\u00e9\u00a0:  Nous nous engageons \u00e0 faire de Facebook un endroit s\u00fbr. Les formes d\u2019expression qui menacent les autres peuvent les intimider, les exclure ou les r\u00e9duire au silence, et ne sont pas autoris\u00e9es sur Facebook.  \n    \n  Confidentialit\u00e9\u00a0:  Nous nous engageons \u00e0 prot\u00e9ger votre vie priv\u00e9e et vos informations. La confidentialit\u00e9 donne aux personnes la libert\u00e9 d\u2019\u00eatre elles-m\u00eames, et de choisir quand et comment elles partagent des informations sur Facebook. Cela facilite la cr\u00e9ation de liens.\n  Dignit\u00e9\u00a0:  Nous pensons que chacun m\u00e9rite les m\u00eames droits et la m\u00eame dignit\u00e9. Nous attendons de chaque personne qu\u2019elle respecte la dignit\u00e9 d\u2019autrui, et qu\u2019elle ne harc\u00e8le pas et ne rabaisse pas les autres. \n    \n\n\n    \n    \n     Nos Standards de la communaut\u00e9 s\u2019appliquent \u00e0 tout le monde, partout dans le monde, et \u00e0 tous les types de contenu. Ils ont \u00e9t\u00e9 con\u00e7us pour \u00eatre exhaustifs. Par exemple, du contenu qui ne serait pas consid\u00e9r\u00e9 comme haineux pourrait malgr\u00e9 tout \u00eatre supprim\u00e9 parce qu\u2019il enfreint une autre politique. Nous savons que les mots ont diff\u00e9rentes significations et n\u2019affectent pas les personnes de la m\u00eame mani\u00e8re selon leur communaut\u00e9 locale, leur langue et leurs origines. Nous faisons tout notre possible pour prendre en compte ces nuances tout en appliquant nos politiques de mani\u00e8re juste et coh\u00e9rente pour chaque utilisateur et sa libert\u00e9 d\u2019expression. Dans le cas de certaines politiques, nous avons besoin de plus d\u2019informations et\/ou de contexte pour faire respecter les politiques conform\u00e9ment aux Standards de la communaut\u00e9. \n\n     Il est possible de signaler du contenu potentiellement en infraction, notamment les Pages, les Groupes, les Profils, le contenu individuel ou des commentaires. Nous les aidons aussi \u00e0 contr\u00f4ler leur propre exp\u00e9rience en leur permettant de\n       bloquer , de   se d\u00e9sabonner \n       ou \n        de masquer  des personnes et des publications.\n       \n\n     La violation de nos Standards de la communaut\u00e9 engendre diverses cons\u00e9quences qui varient en fonction de la gravit\u00e9 de l\u2019infraction et des ant\u00e9c\u00e9dents de la personne sur la plate-forme. Nous pouvons, par exemple, avertir une personne d\u2019une premi\u00e8re infraction, mais si celle-ci persiste \u00e0 enfreindre notre r\u00e8glement, nous pouvons limiter sa capacit\u00e9 \u00e0 publier du contenu sur Facebook ou d\u00e9sactiver son profil. Lorsque nous pensons qu\u2019un contenu repr\u00e9sente un r\u00e9el risque de pr\u00e9judice physique ou une atteinte directe \u00e0 la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 publique, nous pouvons \u00e9galement en informer les autorit\u00e9s. \n     Nos Standards de la communaut\u00e9 d\u00e9finissent ce qui est autoris\u00e9 ou non sur Facebook. C\u2019est dans cet esprit que nous demandons aux membres de la communaut\u00e9 Facebook de suivre ces r\u00e8gles. \n     \nVeuillez noter que la version anglaise des Standards de la communaut\u00e9
